Hi Thomas,

This is a feature request, maybe...

When exabgp generate to send BGP UPDATE messages using ```static route```, it seems to send BGP UPDATE messages per ```route``` respectively even if all of the ```route``` have the same PATH attributes. I've confirmed the messages on the wire using packet capture.

```
neighbor 192.168.0.100 {
        router-id 192.168.0.1;
        local-address 192.168.0.1;
        local-as 65001;
        peer-as 65100;
        hold-time 90;

        family {
                ipv4 unicast;
        }

        static {
                route 172.16.0.0/32 next-hop 192.168.0.1;
                route 172.16.0.1/32 next-hop 192.168.0.1;
        }
}

```
For example, if I use the above config, exabgp would send 2 BGP UPDATE messages. One is for "172.16.0.1/32", the other is for "172.16.0.2/32".

Sometimes I want to send a BGP message with multiple NLRI for converting from pcap.
IMHO, I would be happy if the config like below can be parsed and send one message.
This is just my idea.
```
neighbor 192.168.0.100 {
        -- snip --
        static {
                route [ 172.16.0.0/32 172.16.0.1/32 ] {
                        next-hop 192.168.0.1;
                }
        }
}

```

What do you think?

